  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      301.41,
      525.77,
      314.69
    ],
    "text": "the Sugar Corporation under the said Act since such land released and vested in the Sugar",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      329.16,
      526.25,
      342.44
    ],
    "text": "Corporation is only meant for sugar cane cultivation and nothing else. Therefore, it is the",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      356.66,
      526.08,
      369.94
    ],
    "text": "position of the Respondents that the Petitioner\u2019s position is futile, and the Petitioner cannot ask",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      384.18,
      280.13,
      397.46
    ],
    "text": "for any writ in view of the said judgement.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      419.93,
      227.1,
      433.21
    ],
    "text": "Now I will consider this aspect.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      455.43,
      525.95,
      468.71
    ],
    "text": "It must be borne in mind that an interpretation or judgement given by a court, particularly the",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      482.02,
      526.42,
      496.24
    ],
    "text": "Supreme Court of this country, is part of the unwritten law.1 This is well-recognised principle,",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      8.0,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      510.71,
      525.88,
      523.99
    ],
    "text": "and the other branches of the Government are bound by that and are expected to follow the",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      538.21,
      156.08,
      551.49
    ],
    "text": "same principles.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      573.98,
      526.4,
      587.26
    ],
    "text": "The Supreme Court, having interpreted the State Industrial Corporations Act, under which the",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      601.49,
      526.33,
      614.77
    ],
    "text": "State has released certain lands in favour of the Sugar Corporation; thus, it is the view of the",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      628.98,
      526.1,
      642.26
    ],
    "text": "Supreme Court, that the Sugar Corporation cannot allow or permit another to possess or",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      656.76,
      526.27,
      670.04
    ],
    "text": "cultivate the said land other than for sugar cane cultivation. In addition to that, it also must be",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      684.26,
      525.98,
      697.54
    ],
    "text": "appreciated that a violation thereof may amount to contempt of the Supreme Court. As such,",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 6,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      744.28,
      465.7,
      770.1
    ],
    "text": "1 Walker Sons and Co. (U.K.) Ltd v. Gunatilake and Others [1978-79-80] 1 Sri L.R. 231.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPS-ItalicMT",
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      7.0,
      11.0,
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      777.78,
      303.63,
      806.07
    ],
    "text": "8",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      72.59,
      526.11,
      85.87
    ],
    "text": "the Sugar Corporation granting the Petitioner to possess the land from 1960 is in violation of",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      100.09,
      526.47,
      113.37
    ],
    "text": "the said Supreme Court judgement. Thus, the relief sought by the Petitioner cannot be granted.",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      135.86,
      526.38,
      149.14
    ],
    "text": "Further, whether the land is arable or not, is not a matter to be considered since such land cannot",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      163.36,
      526.16,
      176.64
    ],
    "text": "be given or permitted to be possessed by another since such land belongs to the State; the Sugar",
    "fonts": [
      "TimesNewRomanPSMT"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 7,
    "bbox": [
      72.03,
      191.11,
      526.42,
      204.39
    ],
